The paper deals with the application of low rank matrix completion theory in MIMO radar systems, which involves signal processing, optimization, and statistical inference. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the performance analysis of matrix completion in radar systems, which can be considered as a signal processing and machine learning problem, making cs.SI (Signal Processing) another likely category. The paper also presents theoretical guarantees and sufficient conditions for matrix completion, which can be related to the field of machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. The paper also deals with the design and analysis of radar systems, which can be related to the field of control and systems engineering, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves numerical simulations and experiments, which can be related to the field of numerical analysis and scientific computing, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible category.
